g3303.definition: [μέν] a primary particle; properly, indicative of affirmation or concession (in fact); usually followed by a contrasted clause with {{g1161}} (this one, the former, etc.) Often compounded with other particles in an intensive or asseverative sense.

g3304.definition: [μενοῦνγε] from {{g3303}} and {{g3767}} and {{g1065}}; so then at least

g3305.definition: [μέντοι] from {{g3303}} and {{g5104}}; indeed though, i.e. however

g3306.definition: [μένω] a primary verb; to stay (in a given place, state, relation or expectancy)

g3307.definition: [μερίζω] from {{g3313}}; to part, i.e. (literally) to apportion, bestow, share, or (figuratively) to disunite, differ

g3308.definition: [μέριμνα] from {{g3307}} (through the idea of distraction); solicitude

g3310.definition: [μερίς] feminine of {{g3313}}; a portion, i.e. province, share or (abstractly) participation

g3313.definition: [μέρος] from an obsolete but more primary form of μείρομαι (to get as a section or allotment); a division or share (literally or figuratively, in a wide application)

g3314.definition: [μεσημβρία] from {{g3319}} and {{g2250}}; midday; by implication, the south

g3315.definition: [μεσιτεύω] from {{g3316}}; to interpose (as arbiter), i.e (by implication) to ratify (as surety)

g3316.definition: [μεσίτης] from {{g3319}}; a go-between, i.e. (simply) an internunciator, or (by implication) a reconciler (intercessor)

g3317.definition: [μεσονύκτιον] neuter of compound of {{g3319}} and {{g3571}}; midnight (especially as a watch)

g3318.definition: [Μεσοποταμία] from {{g3319}} and {{g4215}}; Mesopotamia (as lying between the Euphrates and the Tigris; compare {{h763}}), a region of Asia

g3319.definition: [μέσος] from {{g3326}}; middle (as an adjective or (neuter) noun)

g3321.definition: [μεσουράνημα] from a presumed compound of {{g3319}} and {{g3772}}; mid-sky

g3322.definition: [μεσόω] from {{g3319}}; to form the middle, i.e. (in point of time), to be half-way over

g3323.definition: [Μεσσίας] of Hebrew origin ({{h4899}}); the Messias (i.e. Mashiach), or Christ

g3324.definition: [μεστός] of uncertain derivation; replete (literally or figuratively)

g3325.definition: [μεστόω] from {{g3324}}; to replenish, i.e. (by implication) to intoxicate

g3326.definition: [μετά] a primary preposition (often used adverbially); properly, denoting accompaniment; "amid" (local or causal); modified variously according to the case (genitive association, or accusative succession) with which it is joined; occupying an intermediate position between {{g575}} or {{g1537}} and {{g1519}} or {{g4314}}; less intimate than {{g1722}} and less close than {{g4862}}) Often used in composition, in substantially the same relations of participation or proximity, and transfer or sequence.

g3327.definition: [μεταβαίνω] from {{g3326}} and the base of {{g939}}; to change place

g3328.definition: [μεταβάλλω] from {{g3326}} and {{g906}}; to throw over, i.e. (middle voice figuratively) to turn about in opinion

g3329.definition: [μετάγω] from {{g3326}} and {{g718}}; to lead over, i.e. transfer (direct)

g3330.definition: [μεταδίδωμι] from {{g3326}} and {{g1325}}; to give over, i.e. share

g3331.definition: [μετάθεσις] from {{g3346}}; transposition, i.e. transferral (to heaven), disestablishment (of a law)

g3332.definition: [μεταίρω] from {{g3326}} and {{g142}}; to betake oneself, i.e. remove (locally)

g3333.definition: [μετακαλέω] from {{g3326}} and {{g2564}}; to call elsewhere, i.e. summon

g3334.definition: [μετακινέω] from {{g3326}} and {{g2795}}; to stir to a place elsewhere, i.e. remove (figuratively)

g3335.definition: [μεταλαμβάνω] from {{g3326}} and {{g2983}}; to participate; genitive case, to accept (and use)

g3338.definition: [μεταμέλλομαι] from {{g3326}} and the middle voice of {{g3199}}; to care afterwards, i.e. regret

g3339.definition: [μεταμορφόω] from {{g3326}} and {{g3445}}; to transform (literally or figuratively, "metamorphose")

g3340.definition: [μετανοέω] from {{g3326}} and {{g3539}}; to think differently or afterwards, i.e. reconsider (morally, feel compunction)

g3341.definition: [μετάνοια] from {{g3340}}; (subjectively) compunction (for guilt, including reformation); by implication, reversal (of (another's) decision)

g3342.definition: [μεταξύ] from {{g3326}} and a form of {{g4862}}; betwixt (of place or person); (of time) as adjective, intervening, or (by implication) adjoining

g3343.definition: [μεταπέμπω] from {{g3326}} and {{g3992}}; to send from elsewhere, i.e. (middle voice) to summon or invite

g3344.definition: [μεταστρέφω] from {{g3326}} and {{g4762}}; to turn across, i.e. transmute or (figuratively) corrupt

g3345.definition: [μετασχηματίζω] from {{g3326}} and a derivative of {{g4976}}; to transfigure or disguise; figuratively, to apply (by accommodation)

g3346.definition: [μετατίθημι] from {{g3326}} and {{g5087}}; to transfer, i.e. (literally) transport, (by implication) exchange, (reflexively) change sides, or (figuratively) pervert

g3348.definition: [μετέχω] from {{g3326}} and {{g2192}}; to share or participate; by implication, belong to, eat (or drink)

g3349.definition: [μετεωρίζω] from a compound of {{g3326}} and a collateral form of {{g142}} or perhaps rather {{g109}} (compare "meteor"); to raise in mid-air, i.e. (figuratively) suspend (passively, fluctuate or be anxious)

g3350.definition: [μετοικεσία] from a derivative of a compound of {{g3326}} and {{g3624}}; a change of abode, i.e. (specially), expatriation

g3351.definition: [μετοικίζω] from the same as {{g3350}}; to transfer as a settler or captive, i.e colonize or exile

g3353.definition: [μέτοχος] from {{g3348}}; participant, i.e. (as noun) a sharer; by implication, an associate

g3354.definition: [μετρέω] from {{g3358}}; to measure (i.e. ascertain in size by a fixed standard); by implication, to admeasure (i.e. allot by rule)

g3355.definition: [μετρητής] from {{g3354}}; a measurer, i.e. (specially), a certain standard measure of capacity for liquids

g3356.definition: [μετριοπαθέω] from a compound of the base of {{g3357}} and {{g3806}}; to be moderate in passion, i.e. gentle (to treat indulgently)

g3357.definition: [μετρίως] adverb from a derivative of {{g3358}}; moderately, i.e. slightly

g3358.definition: [μέτρον] an apparently primary word; a measure ("metre"), literally or figuratively; by implication, a limited portion (degree)

g3359.definition: [μέτωπον] from {{g3326}} and ops (the face); the forehead (as opposite the countenance)

g3360.definition: [μέχρι]   or μεχρίςfrom {{g3372}}; as far as, i.e. up to a certain point (as a preposition, of extent (denoting the terminus, whereas {{g891}} refers especially to the space of time or place intervening) or conjunction)

g3361.definition: [μή] a primary particle of qualified negation (whereas {{g3756}} expresses an absolute denial); (adverb) not, (conjunction) lest; also (as an interrogative implying a negative answer (whereas {{g3756}} expects an affirmative one)) whether Often used in compounds in substantially the same relations. See also {{g3362}}, {{g3363}}, {{g3364}}, {{g3372}}, {{g3373}}, {{g3375}}, {{g3378}}.

g3362.definition: [ἐὰν μή] i.e. {{g1437}} and {{g3361}}; if not, i.e. unless

g3363.definition: [ἵνα μή] i.e. {{g2443}} and {{g3361}}; in order (or so) that not

g3364.definition: [οὐ μή] i.e. {{g3756}} and {{g3361}}; a double negative strengthening the denial; not at all Compare {{g3378}}.

g3365.definition: [μηδαμῶς] adverb from a compound of {{g3361}} and ἀμός (somebody); by no means

g3366.definition: [μηδέ] from {{g3361}} and {{g1161}}; but not, not even; in a continued negation, nor

g3367.definition: [μηδείς] , including the irregular feminine      μηδεμία, and the neuter      μηδένfrom {{g3361}} and {{g1520}}; not even one (man, woman, thing)

g3370.definition: [Μῆδος] of foreign origin (compare {{h4074}}); a Median, or inhabitant of Media

g3372.definition: [μῆκος] probably akin to {{g3173}}; length (literally or figuratively) length.

g3373.definition: [μηκύνω] from {{g3372}}; to lengthen, i.e. (middle voice) to enlarge

g3375.definition: [μήν] a stronger form of {{g3303}}; a particle of affirmation (only with {{g2229}}); assuredly

g3377.definition: [μηνύω] probably from the same base as {{g3145}} and {{g3415}} (i.e. μάω, to strive); to disclose (through the idea of mental effort and thus calling to mind), i.e. report, declare, intimate

g3378.definition: [μὴ οὐκ]   may ook i.e. {{g3361}} and {{g3756}}; as interrogative and negative, is it not that? Compare {{g3364}}.

g3379.definition: [μήποτε]  or       μή ποτεfrom {{g3361}} and {{g4218}}; not ever; also if (or lest) ever (or perhaps)

g3381.definition: [μήπως]  or       μή πωςfrom {{g3361}} and {{g4458}}; lest somehow

g3382.definition: [μηρός] perhaps a primary word; a thigh

g3383.definition: [μήτε] from {{g3361}} and {{g5037}}; not too, i.e. (in continued negation) neither or nor; also, not even

g3384.definition: [μήτηρ] apparently a primary word; a "mother" (literally or figuratively, immediate or remote)

g3385.definition: [μήτι] from {{g3361}} and the neuter of {{g5100}}; whether at all

g3386.definition: [μήτιγε] from {{g3385}} and {{g1065}}; not at all then, i.e. not to say (the rather still)

g3387.definition: [μήτις]  or       μή τιςfrom {{g3361}} and {{g5100}}; whether any

g3389.definition: [μητραλῴας] from {{g3384}} and the base of {{g257}}; a mother-thresher, i.e. matricide

g3390.definition: [μητρόπολις] from {{g3384}} and {{g4172}}; a mother city, i.e. "metropolis"

g3391.definition: [μία] irregular feminine of {{g1520}}; one or first

g3392.definition: [μιαίνω] perhaps a primary verb; to sully or taint, i.e. contaminate (ceremonially or morally)

g3397.definition: [μικρόν] masculine or neuter singular of {{g3398}} (as noun); a small space of time or degree

g3398.definition: [μικρός] , including the comparative      μικρότεροςapparently a primary word; small (in size, quantity, number or (figuratively) dignity)

g3399.definition: [Μίλητος] of uncertain origin; Miletus, a city of Asia Minor

g3400.definition: [μίλιον] of Latin origin; a thousand paces, i.e. a "mile"
